<div class="container">
    <h1>Why Do We Need a Database?</h1>
    <p>Imagine you're trying to keep track of all your favorite books. You could write them down in a notebook, but what happens when you want to find a book quickly, sort them by author, or share your list with a friend? It becomes hard to manage.</p>

    <p>A <strong>database</strong> helps with all of that. It's a tool that lets us store, search, update, and organize data easily and efficiently.</p>

    <h2>Benefits of Using a Database</h2>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Organization:</strong> Keeps all your data structured and tidy.</li>
        <li><strong>Searching:</strong> Quickly find the information you need.</li>
        <li><strong>Sharing:</strong> Multiple people can use and update the data safely.</li>
        <li><strong>Security:</strong> Protects your data from being lost or accessed by the wrong people.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>Databases are used everywhere – in banks, schools, hospitals, social media, and more – to keep data safe, accessible, and organized.</p>

